description.plain:
THE SCOTTS is the name of the super duo that is composed of Travis Scott and Kid Cudi. The duo was announced alongside the release of their eponymous debut single on April 24, 2020. The single being released under this collaborative title may allude to an imminent project from the duo.

The group’s name is derived from the latter half of Trav’s stage name, Travis Scott, and Kid Cudi’s birth name, Scott Mescudi. Travis has frequently cited Cudi as one of his idols, and the “Scott” in his stage name is named after Cudi.

Before the group’s debut, Travis and Cudi collaborated on several occasions, as outlined below:


Travis, “through the late night” & “way back” (Sep. 2016)
Cudi, “Baptized in Fire” (Dec. 2016)
Travis, “STOP TRYING TO BE GOD” (Aug. 2018)



Travis also has production credits on Kanye West’s “The Morning” and “Guilt Trip” and Quavo’s “LOST,” all of which feature Cudi.

description.plain:
This is a currently unreleased track from Travis Scott and Kid Cudi. The duo first previewed the track on April 23, 2020 on Instagram Live after the self-titled single “THE SCOTTS” was premiered at Travis' live Fortnite concert starting the 23rd of April.

The track’s title is currently unconfirmed and it is unclear if this track will appear on either of the artist’s upcoming records.
